279
00:21:54,839 --> 00:21:59,319
He's into those online videos
where people do stupid things.

280
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:03,240
This week's challenge was
to take as many pills as possible.

281
00:22:03,319 --> 00:22:06,680
We had swimming first thing
in the morning. He couldn't swim,

282
00:22:06,759 --> 00:22:08,839
so I had to pull him out.

283
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:13,480
Thank God I'm a good swimmer.
He could have died.

284
00:22:13,559 --> 00:22:16,359
We need to talk to him.
I'm a mess. God.

285
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,039
Polo! How are you?

286
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,440
Hey, how are you feeling?

287
00:22:23,519 --> 00:22:24,759
I couldn't do it.

288
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:30,039
You can tell him if you want.

289
00:22:44,079 --> 00:22:46,759
Do you guys know anything about Polo?
He's not here today.

290
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:50,519
He was, but he got really sick.

291
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:54,640
He threw up in the locker room.
He made a real mess, right?

292
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,799
Poor him. Anyway...

293
00:22:57,519 --> 00:23:00,920
Yes, we took him home.
He couldn't manage by himself.

294
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,920
What's going on?

295
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,440
What is this about?

296
00:23:19,759 --> 00:23:22,839
Because Polo and Samuel,
they weren't even friends.

297
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:27,240
Lots of other people could have reasons
to get rid of him.

298
00:23:27,799 --> 00:23:29,400
I thought you didn't know Samuel.

299
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,559
I don't, but...

300
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:36,839
people said that he changed
after what happened to Marina.

301
00:23:38,319 --> 00:23:40,519
That he became violent...

302
00:23:40,599 --> 00:23:42,839
and he was hanging out
with the wrong crowd.

303
00:24:20,319 --> 00:24:21,200
Yes?

304
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,079
Hi. Sandra sent me.

305
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:26,160
Good. Thank you very much, kid.

306
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:38,960
What's up, dude? Was it easy or not?

307
00:24:40,559 --> 00:24:42,160
Yes, it was almost too easy.

308
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,240
I already told you.

309
00:24:43,599 --> 00:24:46,759
My mother wouldn't put you in danger.
That's how it will always be.

310
00:24:46,839 --> 00:24:50,559
-I don't know if I want to keep doing it.
-Well, think about it.

311
00:24:51,559 --> 00:24:52,880
She trusts you.

312
00:24:53,839 --> 00:24:57,000
Could we start by paying me
for this trip? I'll decide later.

313
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:02,519
It's just that she's away till tomorrow.
But don't worry.

314
00:25:02,759 --> 00:25:05,960
You'll get the dough right away.
Once you have it, you'll come around.

315
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:22,200
-Please come in, miss.
-Thank you. I'm one of Polo's friends.

316
00:25:25,079 --> 00:25:27,359
-May I?
-Sure.

317
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:50,759
-This way, please.
-Yes, sorry.

318
00:25:52,799 --> 00:25:54,640
My cook made chicken broth.

319
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:58,359
She always says it's the best thing
when you have a stomachache.

320
00:25:58,759 --> 00:26:00,720
Thank you, but you didn't have to come.

321
00:26:02,559 --> 00:26:03,400
Listen...

322
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:06,640
I'll sit down.

323
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:11,079
I know we don't really know each other,

324
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:14,359
and I don't want you to tell me
why you did what you did.

325
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:16,440
You must have your reasons.

326
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:21,759
But I want you to know
that if you need anything, I'm here.

327
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:27,960
And I wouldn't like anything to happen
to you because...

328
00:26:30,960 --> 00:26:33,759
it was hard to pull you out of the pool!

329
00:26:33,839 --> 00:26:35,599
Like... Yes.

330
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,279
Polo, call me.

331
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:50,880
Thank you very much.

332
00:26:51,559 --> 00:26:52,720
It's okay...

333
00:26:52,799 --> 00:26:53,880
For coming to see me.

334
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:57,599
-And for lying in the hospital.
-Yeah.

335
00:26:57,680 --> 00:27:02,640
And for jumping into the pool...
and for the resuscitation thing. All that.

336
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:10,400
You look so cute when you smile.

337
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:13,519
You look very cute. I'm being serious.

338
00:27:13,599 --> 00:27:16,640
Your eyes screw up and...
Are you embarrassed now? Don't be!

339
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,279
Well, I just came to bring you this, so...

340
00:27:21,359 --> 00:27:23,160
I'll give it to your cook
so she can heat it up.

341
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:24,839
It'll taste better when it's hot.

342
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:27,960
I'm leaving. See you in class, okay?
Get some rest.

343
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:42,119
Well, let's save ourselves some work,
shall we? I ask what's up with Polo,

344
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,519
you say nothing, I insist,
I ask you what's up,

345
00:27:44,599 --> 00:27:47,519
you call me annoying,
I tell you to fuck off,

346
00:27:47,599 --> 00:27:48,920
and we'll have an awesome dinner.

347
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,400
-Hilarious.
-Thank you.

348
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:52,920
What's hilarious?

349
00:27:53,359 --> 00:27:54,839
He quit tennis.

350
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,119
I know. Hi.

351
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,119
What a pity, Ander.

352
00:27:58,759 --> 00:28:00,759
You don't look well.

353
00:28:00,839 --> 00:28:02,079
Go back to playing sports.

354
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,880
Do yourself a favor.
I'm just worried about you.

355
00:28:06,039 --> 00:28:08,119
-Hi.
-Hi. Did you order yet?

356
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,440
No. I'm actually not hungry at all.

357
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:11,960
Neither am I.

358
00:28:15,359 --> 00:28:17,559
For fuck's sake, dude,
I told you three times.

359
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:20,599
Should I tell you in another language?
You're being so annoying.

360
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:23,920
-Are you letting us in now or what?
-Hey, Luciano, how are you doing?

361
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,200
They're with me. Let them in, okay?

362
00:28:26,279 --> 00:28:28,160
Thanks for nothing, Luciano.

363
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:30,359
Stop arguing.

364
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:32,559
-Rum and Coke, right?
-Please!

365
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,680
-You?
-Just Coke. Thanks.

366
00:28:34,759 --> 00:28:36,359
Right away!

367
00:28:36,759 --> 00:28:38,759
So let's see what's going on here.

368
00:28:39,319 --> 00:28:40,799
Bitches are out and about.

369
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:46,880
We almost didn't get in
because of that stunt you pulled.

370
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:50,559
I was helping Samuel
get his brother out of prison.

371
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:54,039
Or rather, you wanted to get rid of Carla

372
00:28:54,119 --> 00:28:56,759
using those crazy ideas
that he has in his head.

373
00:28:56,839 --> 00:28:59,240
And all because you like him, right?

374
00:28:59,839 --> 00:29:04,000
Don't go all advice columnist on me.
You have your issue, too.

375
00:29:04,599 --> 00:29:07,720
-My issue?
-Why did you come here, Nadia?

376
00:29:07,799 --> 00:29:10,119
For that oh-so-cool blond snob.

377
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:13,680
That's if he decides to show up,
because Nadia won't do anything about it.

378
00:29:13,759 --> 00:29:16,319
The girl that gets 9.5 out of ten
and goes to complain.

379
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:20,799
But when she likes a guy,
she just sits in the corner waiting

380
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:23,000
or she leaves everything
to the hands of fate.

381
00:29:23,079 --> 00:29:26,440
Listen up, babe.
Fate is a son of a bitch.

382
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:29,559
He has a girlfriend.

383
00:29:30,319 --> 00:29:31,200
Sure.

384
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:34,440
That is his problem and your excuse.

385
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,039
And you?
When are you going to go for it?

386
00:29:44,519 --> 00:29:49,480
Never. Samu likes marchionesses,
and I'm a jester in comparison.

387
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:53,079
So basically, that's your excuse.

388
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:17,359
Samu, are you coming to the club?
I want to talk.

389
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:21,720
Or I'll come by your house,
whatever you want.

390
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:41,920
Ander, that's enough.

391
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,480
Fuck.

392
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,519
Can I tell you something?

393
00:30:47,839 --> 00:30:49,160
I love your eyebrows.

394
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,519
That's cute.

395
00:30:50,599 --> 00:30:53,119
When I was little,
I got teased for having bushy ones.

396
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,839
I got teased, too.

397
00:30:55,519 --> 00:30:59,240
I'm thinking about changing my look a bit.
Maybe shape them a little...

398
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,759
Get a piercing. Something like that.

399
00:31:01,839 --> 00:31:04,799
I think I would like that.
Not so sure about your sister.

400
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,640
All the more reason to do it.

401
00:31:07,519 --> 00:31:08,720
Cheers to that.

402
00:31:14,799 --> 00:31:16,359
Let me tell you something.

403
00:31:17,079 --> 00:31:19,279
That shirt was a great choice.

404
00:31:19,359 --> 00:31:21,200
-Wow, thanks.
-You're welcome.

405
00:31:21,279 --> 00:31:24,240
-At least somebody noticed it.
-I didn't want to say anything.

406
00:31:24,319 --> 00:31:25,480
Why?

407
00:31:25,559 --> 00:31:28,799
-Because that shirt... It's not you.
-Maybe the shirt is me,

408
00:31:29,039 --> 00:31:31,319
and the dark hoodies I wore
were someone else.

409
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:34,759
-Come on, Ander...
-Stay out of it. That's his partner.

410
00:31:35,359 --> 00:31:37,920
All right.
Let's talk about each other's partners.

411
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,559
That is the first thing
you've said to me all night.

412
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:43,559
I've been trying to have dinner
just the two of us all week,

413
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:46,640
and all I've managed to get is this.
No offense.

414
00:31:48,519 --> 00:31:52,799
What shall we do with these two?
Could they be any more boring?

415
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:55,559
You speak Arabic?

416
00:31:55,839 --> 00:31:58,640
Two years in Abu Dhabi, honey. Languages.

417
00:32:02,319 --> 00:32:05,359
I don't get it.
I can't believe you're Nadia's brother.

418
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,279
I'm at the club.

419
00:32:06,359 --> 00:32:09,160
-You're actually charming.
-I sometimes think the same thing.

420
00:32:09,759 --> 00:32:11,400
I just saw your...

421
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:25,039
It's so good reheated.

422
00:32:25,119 --> 00:32:28,079
Who needs a chef when you have
the cheapest microwave available.

423
00:32:29,599 --> 00:32:33,519
You won't see me as a princess
when sauce is dribbling down my chin.

424
00:32:33,759 --> 00:32:36,880
No. I'll do something a lot worse.

425
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:41,400
I'll ask you what this is.
What are we doing?

426
00:32:46,839 --> 00:32:51,279
It's really noisy outside, isn't it?
Nonstop, all around us.

427
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:54,440
It's so quiet in here.

428
00:32:59,039 --> 00:33:00,920
I don't know what we're doing.

429
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:05,880
I'm quite lonely,
and I think you are, too.

430
00:33:07,839 --> 00:33:10,079
So we could be lonely together.

431
00:33:25,319 --> 00:33:27,359
You have some tomato sauce on...

432
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,839
-Where?
-Wait.

433
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:31,960
Here.

434
00:33:35,119 --> 00:33:36,240
Fucking hell...

435
00:33:52,079 --> 00:33:53,039
Thanks.

436
00:33:53,119 --> 00:33:55,000
-Give it to me.
-Don't, Lu.

437
00:33:55,079 --> 00:33:56,839
The dinner was my idea. It's on me.

438
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:59,640
-They're my friends. I want to pay.
-You want to, but you can't!

439
00:34:01,079 --> 00:34:03,400
Can we talk about this at home?
Don't make a scene.

440
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:06,559
-No, I'm going out for a drink.
-What?

441
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:11,159
-I want to go out, not be cooped up.
-Being with me is like being cooped up?

442
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:13,199
I didn't say that.
I said I want to go out for a drink.

443
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,639
It's what you say all the fucking time.

444
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,519
You know what? Do what you want.

445
00:34:18,599 --> 00:34:20,639
You will anyway, whether I like it or not.

446
00:34:21,599 --> 00:34:23,639
Maybe we should get going...

447
00:34:23,719 --> 00:34:25,559
I'm going somewhere.
I have something to do.

448
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:26,960
What do you have to do this late?

449
00:34:27,039 --> 00:34:30,000
So you don't tell your boyfriend
anything either? Fucking great.

450
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:32,880
-Absolutely nothing.
-Ander?

451
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,159
Just like you.

452
00:34:37,239 --> 00:34:38,920
-Guzmán?
-Ander!

453
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,599
Ander!

454
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,719
If you bottle everything up inside,
it'll eat away at you!

455
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:46,159
You really want me
to tell you what's wrong?

456
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:52,039
I want things to go back
to how they were before.

457
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,039
You, me, and Polo.

458
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:02,239
That's all I'm asking for.

459
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,239
Are you coming?

460
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:42,719
