to do anything stupid again.

479
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:36,920
Thank you.

480
00:38:40,679 --> 00:38:42,440
It was an accident, Ander.

481
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:50,719
You don't crack someone's head open
by accident.

482
00:38:56,199 --> 00:38:58,880
But I believe you when you say
that you didn't mean to.

483
00:39:01,679 --> 00:39:03,159
You lost control.

484
00:39:08,760 --> 00:39:10,719
I swear, if only I could go back...

485
00:39:21,639 --> 00:39:23,320
There is one thing we can do.

486
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:32,280
There's an innocent guy rotting in prison
for something he didn't do,

487
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:35,800
at least until the trial begins.

488
00:39:40,199 --> 00:39:42,360
How much money
can you take out of your account?

489
00:40:52,599 --> 00:40:53,440
Ander...

490
00:40:55,639 --> 00:40:59,039
Do you want me to leave?
Is that what's wrong with you?

491
00:41:01,239 --> 00:41:02,119
No...

492
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:07,639
Then why are you acting so strange?

493
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:10,639
It has nothing to do with you, Omar.

494
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:15,559
So why don't you tell me about it?

495
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,320
Trust me, okay?

496
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,119
It'll pass.

497
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:41,760
-Samuel?
-In the bathroom.

498
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:49,559
Hey. You okay?

499
00:41:51,719 --> 00:41:54,480
There was a letter in the mailbox
with your name on it.

500
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:59,440
I'm going to bed.
I'm exhausted. What a day...

501
00:42:33,559 --> 00:42:37,960
-Where's the money from the Sáez family?
-I forgot.

502
00:42:38,679 --> 00:42:41,199
Mrs. Sáez called to tell me
you stole a dress from her.

503
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:43,199
I could have died of shame!

504
00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:45,920
Isn't stealing on the Internet
enough for you anymore?

505
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,880
I don't steal!
I do crowdfunding to launch my designs.

506
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,800
To make clothes for yourself
that you don't sell.

507
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:53,000
How are you going to pay them back?

508
00:42:53,079 --> 00:42:54,320
This has to end.

509
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:57,320
Mom, we'll talk about this at home.
Don't say anything.

510
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,519
I won't say anything.

511
00:42:58,599 --> 00:43:01,719
You are going to say it all.
In front of the whole class.

512
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,559
You'll say that I'm your mother

513
00:43:03,639 --> 00:43:06,280
and that you're here on a scholarship
because we're broke. And proud.

514
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:07,440
-It'll be okay.
-Let go.

515
00:43:07,519 --> 00:43:10,440
Mom, please! Don't ruin everything.

516
00:43:10,519 --> 00:43:12,000
For the first time,

517
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:15,719
I'm starting to feel part of something.

518
00:43:16,159 --> 00:43:17,519
I have friends.

519
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:21,119
And someone that could be
more than a friend.

520
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:22,199
-Mom...
-Hi.

521
00:43:24,519 --> 00:43:25,679
Is there a problem?

522
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:30,400
No.

523
00:43:31,039 --> 00:43:33,639
This young lady's chauffeur
throws his cigarette butts on the ground,

524
00:43:33,719 --> 00:43:35,920
and the school entrance
looks like an ashtray.

525
00:43:36,559 --> 00:43:38,559
Don't worry, I'll talk to him.

526
00:43:38,639 --> 00:43:41,559
Enough of that.
She's a cleaner, not your fucking slave.

527
00:43:41,639 --> 00:43:45,360
-The other day in the bathroom, and--
-Do I stick my nose in your business?

528
00:43:45,679 --> 00:43:48,880
You, with your sunglasses,
your look, and all that?

529
00:43:49,079 --> 00:43:51,039
So much money and so little class.

530
00:43:51,119 --> 00:43:55,119
Listen, Cayetana, it's only eight,
and I'm not in the mood for it,

531
00:43:55,199 --> 00:43:57,000
but you're asking for a slap, honey.

532
00:43:57,079 --> 00:43:58,880
Hey, drug-dealer Barbie.

533
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:00,360
Thanks, Lu.

534
00:44:01,079 --> 00:44:02,920
You don't want to make trouble with me.

535
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:05,000
Careful with badass Barbie.

536
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:07,719
She'd be right at home in my neighborhood.

537
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:10,000
By the way, Latin Barbie...

538
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:11,679
Good day.

539
00:44:18,360 --> 00:44:20,159
I was having a rough time.

540
00:44:21,039 --> 00:44:22,840
My girlfriend,
who I'd been with since I was 12,

541
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:24,159
had left me for someone else, and...

542
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:26,679
it was hard for me
to come to terms with.

543
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:28,880
And, yes,

544
00:44:30,400 --> 00:44:31,440
I tried to...

545
00:44:32,559 --> 00:44:33,639
Well, you know.

546
00:44:34,920 --> 00:44:38,480
But now it's over,
and it made me stronger.

547
00:44:41,039 --> 00:44:43,679
Anyway, I don't know
what this has to do with Samuel.

548
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:50,000
Samuel believed that you were connected
in some way to Marina's death.

549
00:44:50,559 --> 00:44:52,159
That's absurd.

550
00:44:54,440 --> 00:44:57,159
You arrested the culprit yourself, right?

551
00:44:57,239 --> 00:45:00,400
I'm guessing that if you're here,
that means you haven't confessed.

552
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:01,719
You guessed right.

553
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:04,440
I couldn't do it to you.

554
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:07,360
What does that mean, Polo?

555
00:45:09,199 --> 00:45:10,440
I'm a weak person.

556
00:45:11,679 --> 00:45:14,360
If I confess,
I'll end up telling them everything.

557
00:45:15,159 --> 00:45:16,880
That you were an accomplice.

558
00:45:18,199 --> 00:45:21,440
And I don't want to do that to you, love.

559
00:45:24,159 --> 00:45:25,400
Hey.

560
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:28,719
I forgot to reply to your text yesterday.
What did you want to say?

561
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,800
I can't remember.

562
00:45:31,199 --> 00:45:33,599
Don't worry.
It was probably something stupid.

563
00:45:36,719 --> 00:45:38,519
Hi, darling.

564
00:45:38,599 --> 00:45:41,079
So, did you have a good time at the club?

565
00:45:51,719 --> 00:45:54,760
Guzmán! Let us know next time
you're going out, you bastard.

566
00:45:55,239 --> 00:45:56,480
Good morning, class.

567
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:25,000
Subtitle translation by Aline Saba

